.SH NAME
EventSource.open_event \- EventSource: open event
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]open\f[B]\f[R] event of the \f[CR]EventSource\f[R]
interface is fired when a connection with an event source is opened.
.PP
This event is not cancelable and does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqopen\(dq, (event) => { })

onopen = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
